# Unit tests

This project uses `bun` as a test runner.

## How to run unit tests

* `bun run test <path>` - run a test file or test within a folder
* `bun run test` - run all the test suite
* `bun run check` - run linting, typecheck, and tests

Avoid running all the tests. Do it only if specifically asked.

## How to write unit tests

This project uses `bun` as a test runner. 

See the examples below.

File name `my-function.test.ts`:

```typescript
import { describe, expect, it, /* other imports from bun:test */ } from 'bun:test'
import { myFunction } from './my-function.ts

describe('myFunction', () => {
  it('should <test description>', () => {
    // The test code goes here
  })

  // More tests...
})

// Another `describe` block when there are more exported functions to test.
```

A component example with file name `my-component.test.ts`:

```typescript
import { describe, expect, it } from 'bun:test'
import { screen, render } from '@testing-library/react'
import { MyComponent } from 'my-component.ts'

describe('MyComponent', () => {
  it('should <test description>', () => {
    render(<MyComponent /* props */ />)

    // The test code goes here
  })
})
```
